{"lemma":"نَضِرٍ","slug":"نَضِرٍ","root":"ن.ض.ر","root_slug":"ن-ض-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ض-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39990","n39993","n39994"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to glisten, to shine, to strike the eye","examples":[{"text":"وُجُوهٌ يَوْمَئِذٍ نَاضِرَةٌ / إِلَى رَبِّهَا نَاظِرَةٌ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let glisten, to render shiny, to make strike the eye"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"material of best quality such as that strikes the eye (usually gold)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"shiny, glistening, of a fresh colour"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"See the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39990","headword_ar":"نَضُرَ","root":"nDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, A, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDara","text_ar":"نَضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDira","text_ar":"نَضِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, A. K;) the last [also] mentioned by A'Obeyd; (S;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDaArapN","text_ar":"نَضَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) of the first; (S, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDuwrN","text_ar":"نُضُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorapN","text_ar":"نَضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) of the second, (S,) or this is a simple subst., (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorN","text_ar":"نَضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [also of the second;] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDarN","text_ar":"نَضَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K;) [of the third;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDara","text_ar":"اَنْضَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, L, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a tree, A, K, and a plant, A, and foliage, TA, and a colour, K, and a face, IAar, S, Msb, K, and anything, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, beautiful"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bright:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S * [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorapN","text_ar":"نَضْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below] or, when said of a face, tropically used, (A,) signifying as above: (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, beautiful and fresh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful and fine-skinned, so that the blood appeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through the skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hasuna wagaD~a","text_ar":"حَسُنَ وَغَضَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnDr","text_ar":"انضر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a tree,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its foliage became green."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [When said of a man, sometimes signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a state of enjoyment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a plentiful and pleasant and easy state of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with a usage of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDara","text_ar":"نَضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naD~ara","text_ar":"نَضَّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDara","text_ar":"اَنْضَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be mentioned below. And in like manner, when said of life, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became plentiful and pleasant and easy."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDarahu All~`hu","text_ar":"نَضَرَهُ اللّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorN","text_ar":"نَضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nD~rhu","text_ar":"نضّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) or this has an intensive signification; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnDrhu","text_ar":"انضرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, A, K;) when the pronoun relates to the face, (IAar, S, A,) in which case it is tropical, (A,) [or to a tree, or colour, as is implied in the K,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made it beautiful"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bright."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA.) ―         -b2-  When the pronoun relates to a man, the meaning (of the first of these three forms, as mentioned by En-Nadr and Sh and in the Mgh and TA, and of the ↓ second, as mentioned by As, and En-Nadr and Sh, &c., and of the ↓ third, as mentioned in the TA,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made him to have enjoyment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful and pleasant and easy life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naE~amahu","text_ar":"نَعَّمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalhu naADirFA","text_ar":"جَعَلهُ نَاضِرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same]: (A'Obeyd:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDarahu All~`h","text_ar":"نَضَرَهُ اللّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Azdee, Mgh,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~`h","text_ar":"اللّٰه"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nD~rhu","text_ar":"نضّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Hasan El-Muäddib, TA:) signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made his rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Azdee, El-Hasan El-Muäddib, Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Hasan El-Muäddib, TA:) not relating to beauty of the face; (ElAzdee, El-Hasan El-Muäddib, Mgh, TA:) but is similar to the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uTolubuwA AlHawaAy^ija A_ilaY","text_ar":"اُطْلُبُوا الحَوَايِجَ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HisaAni Alwujuwhi","text_ar":"حِسَانِ الوُجُوهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which see explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wjh","text_ar":"وجه"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (El-Hasan El-Muäddib, TA.) As cites this verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"naD~ara A@ll~`hu A^aEoZumFA dafanuwhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        bisijisotaAna TaloHapa AlT~alaHaAti"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God grant enjoyment to bones which they have buried in Sijistán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I mean)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Talhat-et- Talahát"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDara A@ll~`hu EabodFA samiEa maqaAlatiY fawaEaAhaA vum~a A^ad~AhaA","text_ar":"نَضَرَ ا@للّٰهُ عَبْدًا سَمِعَ مَقَالَتِى فَوَعَاهَا ثُمَّ اَدّاهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilY mano yasomaEahaA","text_ar":"اـِلى مَنْ يَسْمَعَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, S, * A, * Mgh, * TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naD~ara","text_ar":"نَضَّرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sh, S, in which latter we read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@moraA^a","text_ar":"ا@مْرَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbdA","text_ar":"عبدا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and A, in which we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EbdA","text_ar":"عبدا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and Mgh; the reading ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nD~r","text_ar":"نضّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone being given in the copies which I have of the S and A;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God cause to have enjoyment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plentiful and pleasant and easy life,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the servant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man, who hears what I say, and keeps it in mind, then conveys it to him who hears it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, Mgh, in explanation of the latter reading, and TA, in explanation of both readings:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make to have a good rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Mgh, in explanation of the former reading.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","Fr","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n39993","headword_ar":"نَضْرٌ","root":"nDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDaArN","text_ar":"نُضَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDaAr","text_ar":"نَضَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDiyrN","text_ar":"نَضِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDaru","text_ar":"اَنْضَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K [without tenween, though this is not shown in the K, as it is originally an epithet, though it may be obsolete as an epithet,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niDaArN","text_ar":"نِضَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Es-Sukkaree:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niSaArN","text_ar":"نِصَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Es-Sukkaree:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally the former:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl. [of pauc.] (of the first, S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anoDurN","text_ar":"اَنْضُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niDaArN","text_ar":"نِضَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or (so accord. to the S and A, but in the K, and) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuDaArN","text_ar":"نُضَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) of gold &c., (A,) or of native or unwrought gold or silver, (Lth, K,) and of wood, (Lth,) or of anything: (S:) and is used as an epithet, applied to gold (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorapN","text_ar":"نَضْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naDorN","text_ar":"نَضْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a molten piece of gold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","Lth"]},{"entry_id":"n39994","headword_ar":"نَضِرٌ","root":"nDr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naADirN","text_ar":"نَاضِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}